</style></head><body style=" font-family:'Cantarell'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;">
<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;"><span style=" font-weight:600;">Spirit filled preaching is the bold proclamation of the Gospel of Jesus Christ.</span></li>
<li style=" font-weight:600;" style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;"><span style=" font-weight:400;">Peter and these apostles are preaching the exact same message that Jesus had been executed for shortly prior. The boldness of that should be an example of how truthful our preaching should be even in these days.</span></li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Preaching is not meant to entertain, make you feel better about yourself, make you laugh, etc. It is about teaching the truth of God without consideration of what will hurt the pocketbook or attending population of the church.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Preaching should be primarily targeting the Gospel of Jesus Christ and bringing that root truth.</li></ul></body></html>